data(nyc_airbnb)

nyc_airbnb = 
  nyc_airbnb |> 
  rename(borough = neighbourhood_group, neighborhood = neighbourhood) |> 
  mutate(stars = review_scores_location/2)

Brainstorm Questions

  • Where are AirBnbs most expensive?
    • Borough? Neighborhood?
    • Do other factors (room type) affect price? What about rating?
  • How long are AirBnbs active?
    • Are AirBnBs illegal and do they get shut down?
  • Which units have the most avilability?
  • How is review score impacted by location?

What boroughs have the most expensive AirBnBs?

nyc_airbnb |>
  group_by(borough) |>
  summarize(
    mean_price = mean(price, na.rm = TRUE),
    med_price = median(price, na.rm = TRUE),
    min_price = mean(price, na.rm = TRUE),
    max_price = mean(price, na.rm = TRUE)
  )
## # A tibble: 5  5
##   borough       mean_price med_price min_price max_price
##   <chr>              <dbl>     <dbl>     <dbl>     <dbl>
## 1 Bronx               82.8        65      82.8      82.8
## 2 Brooklyn           120.         90     120.      120. 
## 3 Manhattan          180.        137     180.      180. 
## 4 Queens              94.7        75      94.7      94.7
## 5 Staten Island      128.         75     128.      128.

Manhattan has both most expensive AirBnBs on average, and the max in the entire data set. Staten Island has a few exceptionally highly priced AirBnBs that pull its mean above that of Brooklyn, though the latter has a higher median price. The lowest priced AirBnBs are in the Bronx.

What Manhattan neighborhoods have the most expensive AirBnBs?

nyc_airbnb |>
  filter(borough == "Manhattan") |> 
  group_by(neighborhood) |>
  summarize(
    mean_price = mean(price, na.rm = TRUE),
    n_obs = n()
  ) |> 
  arrange(desc(mean_price))
## # A tibble: 32  3
##    neighborhood      mean_price n_obs
##    <chr>                  <dbl> <int>
##  1 Tribeca                 353.   156
##  2 Flatiron District       319.    90
##  3 NoHo                    302.    78
##  4 Greenwich Village       258.   383
##  5 SoHo                    256.   356
##  6 Midtown                 251.   958
##  7 West Village            239.   780
##  8 Chelsea                 233.  1072
##  9 Theater District        232.   173
## 10 Battery Park City       221.    65
## #  22 more rows

Tribeca has the highest average AirBnB price, followed by the Flatiron District and NoHo.

Making a Map

nyc_airbnb |>
  filter(
    price < 1000, 
    room_type == "Entire home/apt",
    borough == "Manhattan"
  ) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = lat, y = long, color = price)) +
  geom_point()

Making a Map

nyc_airbnb |>
  filter(
    price < 1000, 
    room_type == "Entire home/apt",
    borough == "Manhattan"
  ) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = lat, y = long, color = price)) +
  geom_point()

nyc_airbnb |>
  filter(
    price < 1000, 
    room_type == "Entire home/apt",
    borough == "Manhattan"
  ) |>
  sample_n(50) |> 
  leaflet() |> 
  addTiles() |> 
  addMarkers(~lat, ~long)
